This paper deals with graphical models and their factorization properties, which are commonly studied in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses information theory and conditional independence, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
